history.text: Hello. Have you seen the movie Frozen by chance? One of the best animated musicals to come from Disney in many years.
I didn't care for Olaf
Fair point, the music was good
Did you like the animation at all? Pretty smooth work from Disney.
Yeah but they did that face thing where everyone looks the same.
Eh they do that to save time and money. Didn't really come off all that bad for this movie.
It made making the merch easier, that's for sure. :)
It gets people interested in it. All the toys, dresses and cups...
Disney definitely wants to draw in the next gen and keep that legacy going.
Yeah and still keeping the old gen with the Musical coming to Broadway (soon tm?)
Broadway is where they found Idina (Elsa's VA) so that's a whole full circle thing
Her voice actor was pretty awesome!
Clear voice and decent tone range to.
... as long as she's not outside in the cold, or thrown off by Travollta. But I digress.
My pitch for a sequel would be Elsa vs. Charlie from Firestarter. Cryokinesis vs. pyrokinesis.
I'd kind of like to see Elsa vs the girl from Brave
Her hair would look so weird frozen stiff! :p
Would turn curly stiff! Too much hair spray. :)
Still think when Elsa turns 21 she will make a decent Queen. Albeit a little Cold hearted!
I know her parents weren't planning on yknow, dying, but they could have still left some instructions on the whole kingdom thing
No one really plans on dying but yeah a little instruction book on how to run a kingdom might of come in handy
Also, maybe a note or two on 'the trolls can probably help with the cryokinesis.' But then we wouldn't have the movie
I just wish Elsa didn't feel so bad hurting her sister with the cryokinetic magic
i wish Marshmallow had had more screen time.
I think he had a decent amount of screen time. Kept him sort of mysterious?
True.
Kind of upsetting when he chased anna away though....
He was doing what he was made for, sadly. Poor Elsa
